docs.lead_paragraph: THE child model, one of the last practitioners of laissez- faire business philosophy, has three months more of unrestricted freedom. On Oct. 1, legislation enacted in Albany last spring goes into effect, thereby ending the open violations of the state labor law that generally prohibits children under 14 years from working.

headline.main: The Typical Income Is From $6,000 to $10,000 a Year; Mothers Often See Careers as Step to Glamour Setting for Distortions
